4.2.6 Up to DKK 10,000 is payable in compensation for treatment of
acute dental damage arising during the period of travel as a result
of an accident. The dental treatment must have commenced abroad, but
may, if necessary, be completed once the injured party has returned
to his/her country of residence.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
4.2.7 In the event of death, payment is made to the closest
relative(s). In this context, 'the closest relative(s)' is taken to
mean the insured's spouse or, if the insured is not married, his/her
life partner with whom he/she has shared an address for at least six
months. If the insured has neither a spouse nor a life partner,
payment will be made to his/her children.
.sp 3mm
If the insured does not have a spouse/partner or children, the sum
payable on death is limited to DKK 12,000.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
accident has led to death within one year of the date of the
injury. The sum payable on death is DKK 1,000,000. The sum payable
on the death of persons under the age of 18 is
DKK 20,000. If disability compensation has been paid in connection
with the same accident, the sum paid will be deducted from the sum
paid on death.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
4.2.2 Disability compensation is payable when an accident has
resulted in permanent medical disability of at least 5%, and the
condition is stationary. Compensation is payable up to three years
from the date of the injury. If the condition is not stationary at
this time, the compensation payable will be determined on the basis
of the condition at this time, irrespective of whether the condition
becomes stationary at a later date, involving a greater or lesser
degree of disability.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
4.2.3 The insurance sum payable amounts to DKK 1,000,000 in the case
of complete disability (100%). The compensation payable amounts to the
percentage of the maximum insurance sum that corresponds to the
established degree of disability.
.br
The degree of disability shall be determined in accordance with the
disability table that the National Board of Industrial Injuries in
Denmark applies at the time of the injury. If the degree of
disability cannot be directly established using the disability table
applied by the National Board of Industrial Injuries in Denmark, the
injured party's degree of medical disability shall be determined
using principles corresponding to those on which the disability
table is based, according to the level of physical functional
impairment.
.br
In all cases, the degree of disability will be established on a
purely medical basis, irrespective of any reduction in earning
capacity, the particular profession of the injured party or other
individual conditions. Loss of earning capacity is not covered.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
4.2.4 The degree of disability cannot exceed 100%.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
4.2.5 An existing disability cannot result in the compensation payable
being set higher than if no such disability had existed.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
