16.0 Baggage
:SKRSLUT.
.br
:SWISS8.
Insurance sum payable: DKK 30,000 per claim.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
16.1 Coverage
:SKRSLUT.
.br
The insurance covers the insured's financial losses for those items he/she
takes with him/her on the journey or purchases at the destination, which
are lost through fire, burglary, open theft or robbery.
.br
Items that the insured brings with him/her but which belong to his/her
employer are also covered by the insurance, but only if no compensation
is payable through another policy or a different agreement.
.br
Moreover, the insurance covers loss of all baggage, theft from baggage
or damage to baggage checked by an airline.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
16.1.1 Definitions
.of 5mm
*¤Burglary is deemed to exist when the thief has gained access to a
responsibly locked building or entered same using an opening not
intended for use as an entrance.
.of
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤Open theft is deemed to exist in the event of theft of items in
the immediate surroundings of the insured, if the insured observed
the theft at the moment that the perpetrator took the item(s) and
immediately raised the alarm, or if the theft was witnessed by other
persons present at the time.
.of
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤Robbery is deemed to exist in the event that the insured is
relieved of or forced to hand over items or valuables through
violence or the threat of the immediate use of violence.
.of
.sp 5mm
.kp off
:FED.
16.5 Special terms and conditions
:SKRSLUT.
.of 5mm
*¤For stolen or totally destroyed items purchased as new within the
past two years, compensation will be paid in an amount equivalent to
the sum required to purchase new corresponding items.
.of
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤For stolen or totally destroyed items that are more than two years
old, the compensation payable will be equivalent to what it would
cost to repurchase the items in question, less a deduction for the
fall in value attributable to age, use, reduced usability or similar
circumstances.
.of
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤The company may choose to have the damaged items repaired or only to
pay a sum corresponding to the price of having the items repaired.
.of
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
16.6 Reporting claims
:SKRSLUT.
.br
On returning home, a claim report is to be submitted to Privatsikring
together with documentation for the lost items.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
With regard to the loss of all baggage, theft of items from baggage or
damage to baggage, refer to the regulations concerning checked baggage
published on the individual airline's websites. Please note that the
airlines have specific regulations concerning what may be packed in
checked luggage with regard to valuables, electronic equipment, foods
and the like.
.br
The PIR report from the airline must be submitted together with the claim.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
If theft, loss or damage to baggage is discovered subsequent to arrival
at the destination or return home, the airline/airport is to be
contacted with a view to requesting confirmation that the grounds for
the claim arose while the baggage was in the possession of the airline.
*¤theft from unlocked motor vehicles, caravans, pleasure craft or tents
.of
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤damage attributable to inappropriate packing and standard treatment
of suitcases and other baggage
.of
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤theft from or damage to the insured's checked baggage, where the
items are covered by the airline regulations concerning items that
are not to be checked. Generally speaking, airlines accept no
liability whatsoever if the insured checks personal effects
including money, keys, medicine, glasses/sunglasses, jewellery, pearls
and precious metals, computers and other personal electronic
equipment, mobile phones, musical instruments, securities, passports
and other identification documents, or damage to or caused by
foods, bottles, glass and similar items packed in the baggage. The
insured should contact the individual airline for
additional information concerning checked baggage.
.of
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤theft of baggage left without adequate supervision. The insured
must not leave baggage unattended - not even for a short time - unless
it is locked in a building, motor vehicle, left luggage locker or similar.
.of
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
